## 10. Decisions log

- **Day ends on button press, not on node entry.** The player clicks `Finish the Day`
  (or a shelter day-ending action triggers it). Entering a node transitions to
  Adventure mode but does not by itself increment the day counter. (MAP.gdd §8 will
  need a light update to reflect this — the arrival-commits model is replaced by
  explicit confirmation.)
- **"Slaughter" replaces "Conquer."** Renamed for flavor consistency. Uses waves
  (2/3/4/—/5 at LV1/2/3/5), not kill-counts. The old "30–80 kills" spec would take
  5–8 minutes at a 6-foe arena cap. Final-wave +1 foe level is **capped at foe level 8**.
- **Only BOSS timer = death.** For all other mission types, failing to achieve the
  goal means no reward and the node remains unconquered — the player survives.
  This prevents a single bad RNG roll in Collection/Protect/Destroy from ending a
  run, while the BOSS timer preserves high-stakes drama for the fights that matter.
- **Plantation stays despite VOID devour.** The tension between "secure a deeper
  node for longevity" and "water aggressively before it's eaten" is intentional,
  not a bug. Mundane shelters still allow plant-tending.
- **Traders & wanderers leave after 5 days.** The player can't hoard NPCs
  indefinitely; there's a window to trade/recruit, then they're gone.
- **Permadeath.** This is a rogue-like. Death = run over. No continues.
- **Boss recruitment is a major feature.** LV4 bosses double as playable protagonists.
  Each needs both a boss encounter kit and a balanced player-character kit. Scope
  accordingly.
- **Wish is deferred.** The shelter's third day-ending action is reserved; the
  Rest/Sharpen pair covers the immediate needs (survival vs. power).
- **Protect objective has its own HP.** The core does not regenerate between waves,
  so the player cannot fully ignore it.
- **Run performance gates LV5/LV6.** Five tracking dimensions feed into the endgame
  content; specifics TBD.
- **Switch Protagonist is the core team mechanic.** Tab (12 s CD) cycles through the
  3-protagonist sequence. HP ratio is inherited; background protagonists' CDs tick at
  ⅕ speed to prevent cycling abuse. Landing effects give each switch tactical weight.
- **Universal mission time limit.** All four non-BOSS mission types share the same
  time limit (base 40 s at LV1, scaled by level multiplier). Previously only Protect
  had an explicit timer — now Collection, Destroy, and Slaughter all race the clock.
- **Blessing actions consume stamina.** Rest / Sharpen Weapon / Sharpen Armor set
  stamina to 0 in addition to consuming the Blessing and ending the day. This prevents
  "use Blessing, then still explore on remaining stamina."
- **Jousting is a mock fight.** Stats are copied before the joust and restored after —
  no HP loss, item CDs, or consumables carry back. Both fighters get 200% HP. The
  wanderer's level follows the day-based foe-level table.
- **ATK/DEF are flat additive stats.** Start at 0 (1× multiplier). Sharpen Weapon
  adds +10 ATK; Sharpen Armor adds +10 DEF. Formula: `dmg = base × (100+ATK)/100`;
  `received = incoming × 100/(100+DEF)`. Replaces the old percentage-based Train.
- **(v0.3.7) BOSS is structural, not rolled.** Mission types roll 60:15:10:10 over
  Collection/Protect/Destroy/Slaughter for LV1/2/3/5 nodes; LV4 and LV6 are always
  BOSS. (The old "~5%" was a share estimate that T30 mistook for a roll weight.)
- **(v0.3.7) Combat entry costs the whole day.** Entering any combat node (new or
  re-attempt) depletes all stamina; failure bounces the player back to the previous
  position with 0 stamina. One combat per day — matches the ≤90-min run budget.
- **(v0.3.7) Only destinations trigger content** (§1.3). Pass-through is inert; paths
  cannot cross unvisited nodes or unconquered combat nodes; NPC windows start on
  first entry as destination.
- **(v0.3.7) The VOID kills.** A player whose node is devoured at day-end dies — the
  third death source alongside combat death and boss-timer expiry. The Finish-the-Day
  confirmation warns on flickering ground.
- **(v0.3.7) Zone-6 foe levels are per-node** (LV5 → 7, LV6 core → 8); the day-based
  table stops at the singularity. In-void, the hidden day still advances (CDs, perish,
  stamina normal; no NPCs or plantations inside).
- **(v0.3.7) Victory-loot demo:** Collection = cores kept + 10 s grace (all foes die on
  goal); Protect/Destroy = 1 random wonder item; Slaughter = choose +10 ATK or +10 DEF.
  Per-type loot design is TODO (TBD registry). Collection failure keeps collected cores.
- **(v0.3.7) Joust is a party fight with copied stats.** Tab allowed; both sides get a
  ×2 max-HP multiplier (on top of the wanderer's foe-level scaling — supersedes the
  old "additive, not multiplicative" note); a joust KO is not permadeath.
- **(v0.3.7) In-run character leveling removed.** WonderPages are renamed **wonder
  cores** — the single run currency, not an XP track. Protagonist growth = Blessings +
  items. Permanent HP/ATK/DEF pools are additive (max HP in percentage points: two
  full-HP Rests → ×1.10 then ×1.20, not compounding).
- **(v0.3.7) XX-S shelters are basics-only.** Blessed with build mod + item assignment
  + one day-ending action; never plantation/trader/wanderer.
- **(v0.5.0) Reward delivery = instant.** Combat rewards apply the moment the goal is
  achieved (with a HUD toast); §1.2's "delivery TBD" resolved as the prototype default.
  Collection credits each core ON PICKUP (so they're kept on a timer failure, per §2.3)
  and its success bundle carries zero cores — no double-count.
- **(v0.5.0) Collection pacing prototype default:** 3 cores on the field at once; an
  untouched core despawns after 12 s and respawns elsewhere (all placement from the
  mission's DetRandom sub-stream); on goal, foes die and a 10 s grace window lets the
  player grab leftovers.
- **(v0.5.0) Destroy objectives prototype default:** stationary targets, HP = 60 ×
  (1/1.5/2/2.5 per LV1/2/3/5), placed from the mission sub-stream on platforms/ground.
  Objectives are hittable like foes but never count toward the ambient spawn cap.
- **(v0.5.0) Protect core aggro (Q10 default):** foes keep chasing the player, but any
  foe within contact range of the Condensed Wonder Core chips it on the core's own
  0.9 s cooldown (per-hit = 18 × the foe level's ATK mult) — ignoring the fight still
  loses the core. Core is not healable (healing stays TBD).
- **(v0.5.0) No in-Adventure Map button yet** (§1.1/§1.2): the map is a separate scene,
  so a view-only overlay needs a SubViewport/snapshot — deferred for combat AND "?"
  events. Finish-the-Day gating (locked until the goal / terminal event choice
  resolves) IS implemented; shelters keep their free "Back to Map" (that's movement,
  not a map view).
- **(v0.5.0) "?" events run through a generic EventRunner** (T30 §7): authored
  `EventDef` pages of choices → composed verb effects (grant cores / heal / grant item /
  nothing); the event for a node is picked deterministically from the run seed. Three
  placeholder events ship as the pipeline proof.
- **(v0.5.0) Day-end visibility:** the map shows a one-shot toast summarizing the
  day-end pipeline's effects (new day, what the VOID devoured, stamina restored).
